BT 1 0 0 1 0 39 Tm 12 TL /F1 9 Tf 0 0 0 rg (The phenomenon is Entanglement Sudden Death \(ESD\), first identified by Yu & Eberly \(2004, 2006\) and experimentally) Tj T* (confirmed \(Science 323:598, 2009\). Entanglement does not decay exponentially like coherence. It reaches a hard zero in) Tj T* /F2 9 Tf (finite time) Tj /F1 9 Tf ( -- a sharp cliff, not a gradual slope. The critical decoherence rate for entanglement is strictly lower than the) Tj T* (critical rate for single-system coherence:) Tj T* ET
