BT 1 0 0 1 0 51 Tm 12 TL /F1 9 Tf 0 0 0 rg (This inequality is the First Boundary Condition of the Wike Coherence Law. The law holds. It always held. It applies to) Tj T* /F2 9 Tf (single-system coherence) Tj /F1 9 Tf (. Entanglement is a correlated property between systems and obeys a stricter, more fragile) Tj T* (threshold. This paper derives the mathematics, presents the simulation data, and shows why this boundary condition) Tj T* (explains one of the deepest puzzles in quantum biology: why coherence is found everywhere in warm biological systems) Tj T* (while entanglement is almost never observed.) Tj T* ET
